title: Djokovic beats Nadal for 6th China Open title
text: Photo: Mark Schiefelbein, AP Timea Bacsinszky of Switzerland, left, holds the runners-up trophy and Garbine Muguruza of Spain, right, holds the winner's trophy as they pose for photos after their women's singles final match in the China Open tennis tournament at the National Tennis Stadium in Beijing, Sunday, Oct. 11, 2015. Timea Bacsinszky of Switzerland, left, holds the runners-up trophy... BEIJING (AP) — Novak Djokovic defeated Rafael Nadal 6-2, 6-2 Sunday to win his sixth China Open title and improve his record at the tournament to a sterling 29-0. Timea Bacsinszky of Switzerland, left, holds the runners-up trophy and Garbine Muguruza of Spain, right, holds the winner's trophy as they pose for photos after their women's singles final match in the China Open tennis tournament at the National Tennis Stadium in Beijing, Sunday, Oct. 11, 2015. Timea Bacsinszky of Switzerland, left, holds the runners-up trophy... BEIJING (AP) — Novak Djokovic defeated Rafael Nadal 6-2, 6-2 Sunday to win his sixth China Open title and improve his record at the tournament to a sterling 29-0.
